g authors of older works on the subject. McGlashan was able to verify the facts and write a book from the point of view of the survivors themselves.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 4aHistory -- United States. 7aHISTORY / United States / State & Local / General.2bisacsh1 aHinkle, Bliss McGlashan, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHinkle, George H., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503621121423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503621121/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles